{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"dc64d6d260e2683565fe6e13d60cfbe9fec0fa09"},"timestamp":1426199949,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU2MDkyMzkwNg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/perl-compiler/issues/31","origin":"github"},"title":"stdin io magic not stored: use open qw(:utf8)","message":"Original [issue 29](https://code.google.com/p/perl-compiler/issues/detail?id=29) created by rurban on 2010-08-16T10:25:49.000Z:\n\nThis test program fails with B-C-1.27, B::C\n\ntest2.pl:\n\n```\nuse open qw(:std :utf8);\n$_ = \u003c\u003e;\nprint unpack('U*', $_), \"\\n\";\nprint $_ if /\\w/;\n```\n\nExpected output:\n\n```\n$ echo \"ö\" | perl ./test2.pl\n24610\nö\n```\n\nWith B::C, the german umlaut \"ö\" isn't read as one unicode character but as two unrelated bytes. The \"ö\" isn't recognized as a word character.\n\n```\n$ perlcc -o test2 test2.pl\n$ echo \"ö\" | ./test2\n19518210\n```\n\nUsed versions:\n- perl v5.10.1 (*) built for i486-linux-gnu-thread-mult\n  (from Ubuntu 10.04)\n- B::C version 1.27","files":null}]}